This paper proposes a new way to self-adjust the mutation rate in population-based evolutionary algorithms, which is a topic related to optimization and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper analyzes the performance of the proposed algorithm on the OneMax test function, which is a classic problem in the field of optimization and search algorithms, suggesting that it could also be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also presents a theoretical analysis of the algorithm's performance, which could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
